---
export const prerender = true;
import Layout from '../components/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About HeaderLab — Open-source security toolkit"
  description="HeaderLab is a free, open-source security toolkit for developers and security professionals. Privacy-first, honest scoring, community-driven."
>
  <article class="about">
    <header class="about-intro">
      <h1>About HeaderLab</h1>
      <p class="about-lead">
        A free, open-source security toolkit for developers and security professionals.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="about-content">
      <p>
        The tools focus on web security headers — checking what you have, building
        what you need, and auditing what's deployed. Everything runs in your browser.
      </p>

      <h2>What HeaderLab stands for</h2>

      <h3>Privacy first</h3>
      <p>
        No accounts, no tracking, no stored URLs. The site uses cookieless,
        aggregate-only analytics.
      </p>

      <h3>Honest scoring</h3>
      <p>
        HeaderLab doesn't scan its own domain — there's no self-interest involved.
        The scoring rigorously applies industry standards, because real security
        requires nuance. A site can have a CSP and still be wide open; we tell
        you that.
      </p>

      <h3>Open source</h3>
      <p>
        HeaderLab's analysis engines are open source on
        <a href="https://github.com/kadirbg/headerlab" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>.
        The detection logic and scoring rules are public — audit them, fork them,
        send a pull request. The security checks aren't black boxes.
      </p>

      <h2>Want to help?</h2>

      <p>
        HeaderLab is open source, and contributions make it better. If you care
        about web security and want to support it:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Star the repo</strong> on
          <a href="https://github.com/kadirbg/headerlab" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>
          — visibility matters
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Open issues</strong> — share ideas, suggest improvements, request new tools
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Send pull requests</strong> — new tools, refined detection logic,
          documentation, translations
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Share with a friend</strong> — the most useful security tool is
          one developers actually know about
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        Or just say hi: <a href="mailto:hello@headerlab.dev">hello@headerlab.dev</a>
      </p>

      <p class="about-signature">— Kadir BUYUKGUCLU, maintainer of HeaderLab</p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .about {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem 0;
  }

  .about-intro {
    padding: 1.5rem 0 2rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .about-intro h1 {
    font-size: 2.25rem;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    line-height: 1.15;
  }

  .about-lead {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    line-height: 1.55;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .about-content h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin: 2.75rem 0 1rem;
    color: var(--text);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .about-content h3 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0 0.5rem;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
  }

  .about-content p {
    color: var(--text-dim);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .about-content em {
    color: var(--text);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .about-content strong {
    color: var(--text);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .about-content a {
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-color: rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.4);
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }
  .about-content a:hover {
    text-decoration-color: var(--accent);
  }

  .about-content ul {
    color: var(--text-dim);
    line-height: 1.75;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    margin: 0.75rem 0 1.25rem;
  }
  .about-content ul li {
    margin: 0.65rem 0;
  }

  .about-signature {
    margin-top: 2.5rem !important;
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--text-faint) !important;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }
</style>